news.title: Indore civic body yet to achieve 75% target of rainwater harvesting system installation
news.para: IMC Commissioner Pratibha Pal, during a review meeting, on Saturday instructed the officials concerned to geotag all such structures with a rainwater harvesting system installed at its roof.

news.title: Nashik civic body installs rainwater harvest systems in its 70 properties
news.para: ​The civic body’s city engineer Shivkumar Vanjari said the NMC has been taking initiatives to install rainwater harvesting systems at all its buildings in a bid to increase the groundwater level since last year.

news.title: Smart City projects in Mangaluru will be completed by December: Minister
news.para: Various Smart City projects including the new indoor stadium near Urwa Market, development of Mangala Stadium, pedestrian plaza near Clock Tower, International Swimming Pool at Yemmekere, Kadri Park development and smart roads are being expedited, the minister said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body gives more time to apply for plots
news.para: Factors such as the somewhat higher prices for the Vizag layouts and the undeveloped plots (the VMRDA will complete these layouts within 12 months from the date of agreement with allottees) might have led to the lukewarm response.

news.title: DLF's rental arm clocks 10% increase in rent income at Rs 3,350 crore in FY22
news.para: According to an investors presentation, the rental income of DLF Cyber City Developers grew to Rs 3,350 crore during last fiscal year from Rs 3,029 crore in 2020-21.

news.title: Delhi HC dismisses Harsha Buildcom director's plea challenging one year imprisonment
news.para: The high court said the state consumer dispute redressal commission (SCDRC) has adhered to the prescribed procedure and the petitioner director was explained the offence and his plea was recorded after which the findings and sentence had been passed.

news.title: Supertech Ecovillage 2 residents demand that builder urgently completes pending work
news.para: Two boys, cousins aged 12 and 9, fell into a utility shaft covered with just a PVC sheet while playing outside their flat on the ninth floor last Tuesday. Their family said they survived because WiFi cables in the shaft broke their fall.

news.title: Bengaluru: Revenue officials yet to recover Rs 250 crore compensation owed to buyers
news.para: RERA has sent 631 cases to the revenue department to recover the penalty of Rs 258 crore from 125 builders but the revenue department could recover only Rs 8 crore so far and it is yet to recover Rs 250 crore from 614 cases.

news.title: Gurugram: Toll-free number for property ID errors
news.para: The complaints from the call centre will be directed to the officials concerned so that people don’t have to run from pillar to post to get their grievances resolved.

news.title: Bengaluru: This fiscal, BBMP records 50% rise in property tax collection
news.para: According to data shared by the urban local body, the Palike collected Rs 1,786.2 crore till May 26, an increase of 84.2% as against 2020-2021 (May 26).

news.title: In Pune, joint property ownership goes up to 88%; maximum in Maharashtra
news.para: A special initiative by the Pune Zilla Parishad has entailed that out of the 9.27 lakh property cards, nearly 8.15 lakh have names of both men and women.

news.title: Pucca house still a distant dream for half of Madhya Pradesh families
news.para: In the state, only 45% households have a pucca house, showed the fifth round of National Family and Health Survey. In case of rural areas, only 32.6% of households have a pucca house in Madhya Pradesh with over 70% population in these areas, showed survey.

news.title: Maharashtra: Collectors told to speed up MahaRERA recovery orders
news.para: Overall, MahaRERA has listed recovery warrants worth Rs 702. 49 crore against errant developers in 13 districts of the state.

news.title: Mumbai: Court denies pre-arrest bail to directors of K D Developers
news.para: As per the case details, the accused were constructing Ruparel Orion, a residential tower in suburban Chembur. The complainant claimed that he had booked a flat in the building and had also convinced his colleagues purchase flats there.

news.title: Ajnara loses land over non-payment of dues after 11 years in Greater Noida
news.para: "Ajnara Realtech had purchased 72,962 square metres of land from GNIDA in 2011 for about Rs 84.34 crore. After paying 10 per cent of the total money, an installment of 90 per cent of the amount was made which were to be paid twice every year," GNIDA's office on special duty (OSD) Soumya Srivastava said.
